alinas (handballer)|Rodrigo Salinas]]\n*Central back: {{flagicon|ARG}} [[Sebasti\u00e1n Simonet]]\n*Left back: {{flagicon|GRL}} [[Minik Dahl H\u00f8egh]]\n*Left wing: {{flagicon|BRA}} [[Felipe Ribeiro|Felipe Borges]]\n*Pivot: {{flagicon|CHI}} [[Marco Oneto]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n*[http://www.panamhandball.org/index.php?option=com_joomleague&func=showResultsRank&layout=bydiv&p=39 Official website]{{Dead link|date=September 2018 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}\n\n{{American Handball Championship}}\n{{2013 World Men's Handball Championship qualification}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Pan American Men's Handball Championship, 2012}}\n[[Category:Pan American Men's Handball Championship|2012 Pan American Men's Handball Championship]]\n[[Category:2012 in handball]]\n[[Category:2012 in Argentine sport]]\n[[Category:International handball competitions hosted by Argentina|H]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2013}}\n{{Infobox International Handball Competition\n| tourney_name = Pan American Men's Handball Championship\n| year = 2012\n| yearr = \n| other_titles = PanAmericano 2012\n| image =\n| size = \n| caption = \n| country = Argentina\n| dates = 18\u201324 June\n| num_teams = 9\n| confederations = 1\n| venues = 1\n| cities = 1\n| champion = ARG\n| count = 5\n| second = BRA\n| third = CHI\n| fourth = URU\n| matches = 23\n| goals = 1227\n| attendance = \n| top_scorer = {{flagicon|GRL}} [[Minik Dahl H\u00f8egh]]<br><small>(49 goals)</small>\n| player = {{flagicon|CHI}} [[Marco Oneto]]\n| previous = 2010 Pan American Men's Handball Championship\n| next = 2014 Pan American Men's Handball Championship\n}}\n\nThe '''2012 [[Pan American Handball Championship]]''', also called '''PanAmericano 2012''', was the 15th official competition for senior men's national [[Team handball|handball]] teams of North, Center, Caribbean and South America. It was held from 18\u201324 June 2012 in [[Burzaco]], [[Almirante Brown Partido]], [[Argentina]]. It also acted as the qualifying competition for the [[2013 World Men's Handball Championship]], securing three vacancies for the World Championship. A decision was announced during the [[2011 Pan American Games]] that the tournament will consist of 12 teams.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://teamhandballnews.com/2011/10/new-developments-regarding-pathf-competitions/|title=New developments regarding PATHF competitions|date=23 October 2011|work=teamhandballnews.com}}</ref> As the winner of those Pan American Games, Argentina was selected as the host.\n\n== Participating teams ==\nThe participating nations have been announced on 15 May 2012.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.panamhandball.org/index.php?option=com_content&task=view&id=174&Itemid=1|title=Confirmados diez pa\u00edses al Campeonato masculino adulto 2012|date=15 May 2012|work=panamhandball.org|access-date=19 May 2012|archive-url=https://archive.is/20120913092623/http://www.panamhandball.org/index.php?option=com_content&task=view&id=174&Itemid=1#|archive-date=13 September 2012|url-status=dead|df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n!width=50%|Group A\n!width=50%|Group B\n|- \n|valign=top|\n{{hb|ARG}}<br />\n{{hb|CHI}}<br />\n{{hb|GRL}}<br />\n{{hb|USA}}<br />\n{{hb|VEN}}\n|valign=top|\n{{hb|BRA}}<br />\n<s>{{hb|DOM}}</s><br />\n{{hb|MEX}}<br />\n{{hb|PAR}}<br />\n{{hb|URU}}\n|}\n\nThe Dominican Republic team withdrew after the draw, reportedly for financial reasons.<ref>{{cite web|title=2013 Men\u2019s WC Qual|url=http://teamhandballnews.com/wordpress/2013-mens-wc-qual/|publisher=teamhandballnews.com|accessdate=11 January 2013}}</ref>\n\n==Preliminary round==\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n| style=\"background: #ccffcc;\" | &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\n|Team advances to the [[#Final round|Semifinals]]\n|-\n| style=\"background: #ffcccc;\" | &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\n|Team will play [[#Placement matches|Placement Matches]]\n|}\n\n''All times are local ([[Time in Argentina|UTC\u22123]])''\n\n===Group A===\n{{Handball ta