malaysia/posts/10156846035326237|title=Ministry of Health of Malaysia|via=Facebook|accessdate=21 March 2020}}</ref>\n|-\n| 2\n| 358\n| 17 March 2020\n| {{MYS}}\n| Male\n| 60\n| {{flagicon image|Flag of Sarawak.svg}} Sarawak General Hospital\n| Had chronic illness. He showed symptoms of fever, coughing and shortness of breath on 7 March 2020.\n|-\n| 3\n| 152\n| 20 March 2020\n| {{MYS}}\n| Male\n| 58\n| {{flagicon image|Flag of Sabah.svg}} Tawau Hospital\n| Part of the religious gathering cluster. Hospitalised on 9 March 2020 when he showed [[severe acute respiratory infection]] (SARI) symptoms.\n|-\n| 4\n| 238\n| 21 March 2020\n| {{MYS}}\n| Male\n| 50\n| {{flagicon image|Flag of Malacca.svg}} Malacca General Hospital\n| Part of the religious gathering cluster. Hospitalised on 12 March 2020 when he showed SARI symptoms.\n|-\n| 5\n| 1031\n| 18 March 2020\n| {{MYS}}\n| Female\n| 79\n| {{flagicon image|Flag of Sarawak.svg}} Borneo Medical Centre\n| Hospitalised after experiencing fever and coughing for five days. Had contact with two other positive cases, her son and daughter.\n| rowspan=\"6\" | <ref name=\"my0322\"/>\n|-\n| 6\n| 1032\n| 21 March 2020\n| {{MYS}}\n| Female\n| 40\n| {{flagicon image|Flag of Sarawak.svg}} Sarawak General Hospital\n| Hospitalised since 7 March 2020 after she showed symptoms of fever and coughing.\n|-\n| 7\n| 290\n| 21 March 2020\n| {{MYS}}\n| Male\n| 57\n| {{flagicon image|Flag of Kuala Lumpur Malaysia.svg}} Kuala Lumpur Hospital\n| Had a travel history to [[Vietnam]] and had contact with a positive case from the religious gathering cluster.\n|-\n| 8\n| 781\n| 21 March 2020\n| {{MYS}}\n| Male\n| 69\n| {{flagicon image|Flag of Kelantan.svg}} Raja Perempuan Zainab II Hospital\n| Part of the religious gathering cluster. Hospitalised on 16 March 2020 when he showed fever symptom since 12 March 2020.\n|-\n| 9\n| 890\n| 22 March 2020\n| {{MYS}}\n| Male\n| 48\n| {{flagicon image|Flag of Perlis.svg}} Tuanku Fauziah Hospital\n| This is the first medi