d\n|-\n! rowspan=\"3\" | [[Minions (Despicable Me)|Minions]]\n| [[Pierre Coffin]]<br>{{small|(Kevin, Stuart, Bob, Tim, Mark and Phil)}}\n| rowspan=\"2\" | Pierre Coffin\n| rowspan=\"3\" colspan=\"4\" | Pierre Coffin\n|-\n| [[Chris Renaud (animator)|Chris Renaud]]<br>{{small|(Dave)}}\n|-\n| [[Jemaine Clement]]<br>{{small|(Jerry)}}\n| Chris Renaud<br>{{small|(Additional and Evil Minions)}}\n|-\n! Victor \"Vector\" Perkins\n| [[Jason Segel]]\n| colspan=\"5\" style=\"background:#d3d3d3;\" |\n|-\n! Mr. Perkins\n| [[Will Arnett]]\n| colspan=\"5\" style=\"background:#d3d3d3;\" |\n|-\n! Miss Hattie\n| [[Kristen Wiig]]\n| colspan=\"5\" style=\"background:#d3d3d3;\" |\n|-\n! Marlena\n| [[Julie Andrews]]\n| {{N/A|''Silent cameo''}}\n| Julie Andrews\n| style=\"background:#d3d3d3;\" |\n| {{N/A|''Silent cameo''}}\n| Julie Andrews\n|-\n! Lucy Wilde\n| style=\"background:#d3d3d3;\" |\n| colspan=\"2\" | Kristen Wiig\n| colspan=\"3\" style=\"background:#d3d3d3;\" |\n|-\n! Eduardo Perez / El Macho\n| style=\"background:#d3d3d3;\" |\n| [[Benjamin Bratt]]\n| colspan=\"2\" style=\"background:#d3d3d3;\" |\n| {{N/A|''Silent cameo''}}\n| style=\"background:#d3d3d3;\" |\n|-\n! Silas Ramsbottom\n| style=\"background:#d3d3d3;\" |\n| colspan=\"2\" | [[Steve Coogan]]\n| colspan=\"3\" style=\"background:#d3d3d3;\" |\n|-\n! Antonio P\u00e9rez\n| style=\"background:#d3d3d3;\" |\n| [[Mois\u00e9s Arias]]\n| colspan=\"4\" style=\"background:#d3d3d3;\" |\n|-\n! Balthazar Bratt\n| colspan=\"2\" style=\"background:#d3d3d3;\" |\n| [[Trey Parker]]\n| colspan=\"3\" style=\"background:#d3d3d3;\" |\n|-\n! Dru\n| colspan=\"2\" style=\"background:#d3d3d3;\" |\n| Steve Carell\n| colspan=\"3\" style=\"background:#d3d3d3;\" |\n|-\n! Fritz\n| colspan=\"2\" style=\"background:#d3d3d3;\" |\n| Steve Coogan\n| colspan=\"3\" style=\"background:#d3d3d3;\" |\n|-\n! Clive the Robot\n| colspan=\"2\" style=\"background:#d3d3d3;\" |\n| [[Andy Nyman]]\n| colspan=\"3\" style=\"background:#d3d3d3;\" |\n|-\n! Scarlet Overkill\n| colspan=\"4\" style=\"background:#d3d3d3;\" |\n| [[Sandra Bullock]]\n| style=\"background:#d3d3d3;\" |\n|-\n! Herb Overkill\n| colspan=\"4\" style=\"background:#d3d3d3;\" |\n| [[Jon Hamm]]\n| style=\"background:#d3d3d3;\" |\n|-\n! [[Elizabeth II|Queen Elizabeth II]]\n| colspan=\"4\" style=\"background:#d3d3d3;\" |\n| [[Jennifer Saunders]]\n| style=\"background:#d3d3d3;\" |\n|-\n! Walter Nelson\n| colspan=\"4\" style=\"background:#d3d3d3;\" |\n| [[Michael Keaton]]\n| style=\"background:#d3d3d3;\" |\n|-\n! Madge Nelson\n| colspan=\"4\" style=\"background:#d3d3d3;\" |\n| [[Allison Janney]]\n| style=\"background:#d3d3d3;\" |\n|-\n! Belle Bottom\n| colspan=\"5\" style=\"background:#d3d3d3;\" |\n| [[Taraji P. Henson]]\n|-\n! Jean Clawed\n| colspan=\"5\" style=\"background:#d3d3d3;\" |\n| [[Jean-Claude Van Damme]]\n|-\n! Nunchuck\n| colspan=\"5\" style=\"background:#d3d3d3;\" |\n| [[Lucy Lawless]]\n|-\n! Svengeance\n| colspan=\"5\" style=\"background:#d3d3d3;\" |\n| [[Dolph Lundgren]]\n|-\n! Stronghold\n| colspan=\"5\" style=\"background:#d3d3d3;\" |\n| [[Danny Trejo]]\n|-\n! Wild Knuckles\n| colspan=\"5\" style=\"background:#d3d3d3;\" |\n| [[Alan Arkin]]\n|-\n! Master Chow\n| colspan=\"5\" style=\"background:#d3d3d3;\" |\n| [[Michelle Yeoh]]\n|-\n! TBA\n| colspan=\"5\" style=\"background:#d3d3d3;\" |\n| [[RZA]]\n|}\n* '''Note:''' A grey indicates that the character does not appear in that medium.\n\n==Crew==\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:center;\" \"width:100%;\"\n|-\n! rowspan=\"3\" | Role\n! colspan=\"3\" | Main films\n! colspan=\"2\" | Spin-offs\n|-\n! ''[[Despicable Me]]''\n! ''[[Despicable Me 2]]''\n! ''[[Despicable Me 3]]''\n! ''[[Minions (film)|Minions]]''\n! ''[[Minions: The Rise of Gru]]''\n|-\n! 2010\n! 2013\n! 2017\n! 2015\n! 2021\n|-\n! Director(s)\n| colspan=\"2\" |  [[Chris Renaud (animator)|Chris Renaud]] and [[Pierre Coffin]]\n| Pierre Coffin, [[Kyle Balda]] and Eric Guillon\n| Pierre Coffin and Kyle Balda\n| Kyle Balda, Brad Ableson and Jonathan del Val<ref name=Minions2Crew />\n|-\n! Producer(s)\n| [[Chris Meledandri]], John Cohen and [[Janet Healy]]\n| colspan=\"3\" | Chris Meledandri and Janet Healy\n|Chris Meledandri, Janet Healy and Chris Renaud\n|-\n! Executive Producer(s)\n| [[Sergio Pablos]] and Nina Rappaport\n| Robert Taylor\n| colspan=\"2\" | Chris Renaud\n| Pierre Coffin\n|-\n! Writer(s)\n| {{small|Screenplay:}}<br />Cinco Paul and Ken Daurio<br />{{small|Story:}}<br />Sergio Pablos\n| colspan=\"2\" | Cinco Paul and Ken Daurio\n| colspan=\"1\" | [[Brian Lynch (writer)|Brian Lynch]]\n| colspan=\"1\" | Matthew Fogel\n|-\n! Composer(s)\n| colspan=\"3\" | [[Heitor Pereira]]<br />{{small|Original Songs and Themes by:}}<br />[[Pharrell Williams]]\n| colspan=\"2\" | Heitor Pereira\n|-\n! Editor(s)\n| Pamela Ziegenhagen-Shefland and Gregory Perler\n| Gregory Perler\n| colspan=\"3\" | Claire Dodgson\n|}\n\n==Film reception==\n{{details|Despicable Me#Reception|Despicable Me  2#Reception|Minions (film)#Reception|Despicable Me 3#Reception|topic=the reception of each film}}\n\n===Box office performance===\nThe film series has grossed a total of more than $3.7 billion, with an average of over $927 million per film,<ref name=\"BOMDM\" /> making the ''Despicable Me'' franchise the [[List of highest-grossing animated films#Highest-grossing animated franchises and film series|highest-grossing animated film franchise]], and the 15th [[List of highest-grossing films#Highest-grossing franchises and film series|highest-grossing film franchise]] of all time.\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"  style=\"width:99%; text-align:center;\"\n|-\n! rowspan=\"2\" | Film\n! rowspan=\"2\" | Release date\n! colspan=\"3\" | Box office revenue\n! colspan=\"2\" text=\"wrap\" | Box office ranking\n! rowspan=\"2\" | Budget\n! rowspan=\"2\" | {{nowrap|{{Abbr|Ref(s)|References}}}}\n|-\n! North America\n! Other territories\n! Worldwide\n! All time<br />North America\n! All time<br />worldwide\n|-\n| ''[[Despicable Me]]''\n| July 9, 2010\n| $251,513,985\n| $291,600,000\n| $543,113,985\n| 110\n| 163\n| $69 million\n| <ref name=\"BOMDM1\">{{cite web|title=Despicable Me|url=http://www.boxofficemojo.com/movies/?id=despicableme.htm|publisher=Box Office Mojo|accessdate=February 15, 2018}}</ref>\n|-\n| ''[[Despicable Me 2]]''\n| July 3, 2013\n| $368,061,265\n| $602,700,620\n| $970,761,885\n| 38\n| 34\n| $76 million\n| <ref name=\"BOMDM2\">{{cite web|title=Despicable Me 2|url=http://www.boxofficemojo.com/movies/?id=despicableme2.htm|publisher=Box Office Mojo|accessdate=February 15, 2018}}</ref>\n|-\n| ''[[Despicable Me 3]]''\n| June 30, 2017\n| $264,624,300\n| $770,175,109\t \n| $1,034,799,409\n| 96\n| 25\n| $80 million\n| <ref name=\"BOMDM3\">{{cite web|title=Despicable Me 3|url=http://www.boxofficemojo.com/movies/?id=despicableme3.htm|publisher=Box Office Mojo|accessdate=June 28, 2019}}</ref>\n|-\n! colspan=2 | ''Despicable Me'' films\n! ${{val|{{#expr:251513985+368061265+264624300}}|fmt=commas}}\n! ${{val|{{#expr:291600000+602700620+770175109}}|fmt=commas}}\n! ${{val|{{#expr:543113985+970761885+1034799409}}|fmt=commas}}\n! colspan=2 |\n! $225 million\n!\n|-\n| ''[[Minions (film)|Minions]]''\n| July 10, 2015\n| $336,045,770\n| $823,352,627\n| $1,159,398,397\n| 49\n| 14\n| $74 million\n| <ref name=\"BOMM1\">{{cite web|title=Minions|url=http://www.boxofficemojo.com/movies/?id=minions.htm|publisher=Box Office Mojo|accessdate=February 15, 2018}}</ref>\n|- \n| ''[[Minions: The Rise of Gru]]''\n| July 2, 2021\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|-\n! colspan=2 | Total\n! ${{val|{{#expr:251513985+368061265+264624300+336045770}}|fmt=commas}}\n! ${{val|{{#expr:291600000+602700620+770175109+823352627}}|fmt=commas}}\n! ${{val|{{#expr:543113985+970761885+1034799409+1159398397}}|fmt=commas}}\n! 18\n! 13\n! $299 million\n! <ref name=\"BOMDM\">{{cite web|title=Franchises - Despicable Me|url=http://www.boxofficemojo.com/franchises/chart/?id=despicableme.htm|publisher=Box Office Mojo|accessdate=November 9, 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Franchise Index|url=http://www.boxofficemojo.com/franchises/?view=Franchise&sort=sumgross&order=DESC&p=.htm|publisher=Box Office Mojo|accessdate=February 15, 2018}}</ref>{{Dead link|date=February 2020}}\n|-\n|}\n\n===Critical and public response===\n{| class=\"wikitable\"  border=\"1\" style=\"width:99%; text-align:center;\"\n|-\n! '''Film'''\n! '''[[Rotten Tomatoes]]'''\n! '''[[Metacritic]]'''\n! '''[[CinemaScore]]'''\n|-\n| ''Despicable Me''\n| 81% (197 reviews)<ref name=\"RTDM1\">{{cite web|title=Despicable Me (2010)|url=http://www.rottentomatoes.com/m/1214097-despicable_me/|publisher=Rotten Tomatoes|accessdate=November 9, 2017}}</ref>\n| 72 (35 reviews)<ref name=\"MCDM1\">{{cite web|title=Despicable Me|url=http://www.metacritic.com/movie/despicable-me|publisher=Metacritic|accessdate=November 29, 2015}}</ref>\n| A<ref name=\"DMcs\">{{cite web | url=http://www.cinemascore.com/ | title=CinemaScore | work=cinemascore.com | accessdate=November 29, 2015}}</ref>\n|-\n| ''Despicable Me 2''\n| 75% (181 reviews)<ref name=\"RTDM2\">{{cite web|title=Despicable Me 2 (2013)|url=http://www.rottentomatoes.com/m/despicable_me_2/|publisher=Rotten Tomatoes|accessdate=December 10, 2017}}</ref>\n| 62 (39 reviews)<ref name=\"MCDM2\">{{cite web|title=Despicable Me 2|url=http://www.metacritic.com/movie/despicable-me-2|publisher=Metacritic|accessdate=November 29, 2015}}</ref>\n| A<ref name=\"DMcs\" />\n|-\n| ''Minions''\n| 55% (216 reviews)<ref>{{cite web|title=Minions (2015)|url=http://www.rottentomatoes.com/m/minions/|publisher=Rotten Tomatoes|accessdate=December 10, 2017}}</ref>\n| 56 (35 reviews)<ref>{{cite web|title=Minions|url=http://www.metacritic.com/movie/minions|publisher=Metacritic|accessdate=November 29, 2015}}</ref>\n| A<ref>{{cite web|last1=Busch|first1=Anita|title=\u2018Minions\u2019 Is No. 2 Top Animated Opener With $115.7M \u2013 Box Office Final|url=http://deadline.com/2015/07/minions-marching-to-114m-to-116m-weekend-box-office-friday-1201473955/|publisher=Deadline|acce